      "writtenOn": "2026-03-26T13:30:32Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Mongo works in a way that it will check each part of the array against the requested value. So for instance, if you check that `arr \u003c 3` and `arr \u003d [1, 2, 3]` then the condition will be checked true. So here, if `comp_flags \u003d [init, init | offline, 0]`, then `comp_flags BITS_ANY_SET init` will eval to true because the array contains a value with `init`, same thing for `comp_flags BITS_ANY_SET offline`, it will eval to true because the bits for `offline` are present in the second element of the array.\n\nWe\u0027ve had discussions about whether it\u0027s a good thing it works this way or not, but ultimately it was easier to implement and take advantage of this logic than force something else.",
      "parentUuid": "24534e52_2c41e90a",
      "revId": "512e9eab49e912bf9b9f77fc4de66b148134eaf6",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
